{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Oxford}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\insrsid14642898\charrsid16072257 {\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \fi-461\li461\ri0\sa240\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin461\itap0\pararsid14642898 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Could you tell me the year of your birth, please?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 1905.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 And the place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Cowley Road{\*\xmlclose}, {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname 
City}}Oxford{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, opposite what is now the hospital.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 How many years did you live in that house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Until 1928, when I was married.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 You didn't have any other houses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 No, always there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Did you have any brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 One sister - the oldest of the family, and one brother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Is the brother younger or older than you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 He's older. I'm the younger by somewhere about 8 years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 You mean there's 8 years between you and your brother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 What was there between your brother and your sister?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 18 months between my brother and my sister.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 When your were born, do you know how old your father was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 I have no idea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Do you have any way to calculate it? For example, do you know how old he was when he died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes, he was 79 when he died, in 1946.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 So in 1905 he would have been about 35.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes, roughly 35. And mother would have been, I think, somewhere 3 years younger than he was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Could you tell me what job he had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes, he was a house painter and decorator.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Who for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 A firm called Longhurst's, who had their establishment, I think, at the corner of {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Divinity Road{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Did he always do that work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes, always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 He never had any other job at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 No, up 'till the time he died he was a house painter and decorator.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 What about your mother? Do you know if she ever worked, or had a job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes, she was a cook, a very good cook, at some of the houses both in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname 
City}}Oxford{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} and out in the country. Where in the country I couldn't say, but I know that she worked at what is now Pullen's Lane. She worked in one of the houses there for a Dr. Vyner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 That was before she married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Before she married, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 And after she married did she ever go to work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Oh, no. It wasn't done in those days!
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Do you think that was both her husband's and her own attitude, that she shouldn't work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Any work whatever! Oh, it would have been a disgrace for my mother to have had to work, in my father's opinion, anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Why do you think that was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 I think it was the attitude of people in those days. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12919142\charrsid3743759 
A woman would only work if she hadn't a husband, or if she had a husband who wouldn't work himself and she'd got to keep a family. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 But this was definitely the opinio
n of people, the wife should not work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 When you were living in that house, up till you married, how many rooms did it have? What sort of house was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Very much the type of this house. Perhaps not quite so many stairs, but there were the usual kitchen, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12919142\charrsid3743759 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759  reception rooms, 3 bedrooms, and a big cellar.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Did you have anybody else living with you? Any relatives, or lodgers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 No, just the family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Did your mother have anyone helping her in the house that she paid, ever?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 She couldn't possibly have afforded it on my father's wage.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Did she do her washing at home, or did she send it out? To a laundry or bagwash?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 She did quite a good bit of it, but to help my grandmother, she used to come once a week and help with the washing. Tha
t gave - my grandmother was a widow - a little bit of pin money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 That's interesting; was that her own mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Did this involve any sort of embarrassment, do you think, that the grandmother was paid?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Not a bit. Not a bit. No. It use
d to be a day that my grandmother came to visit us, and it was one of the joys of my childhood, having my maternal grandmother with me. She was a wonderful woman.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 What sort of person was she, then, in character?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 A placid - as my mother was - a placid, kindly, real grandmotherly woman.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3743759  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 it in her. She had a beautiful face.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 And she used to come once a week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Once a week, yes, because it was the day that she came to stay with us. And again, this was my mother's way of helping out a little tin
y bit. There wasn't an awful lot in it, but I suppose half a crown in those days was quite a little...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 It was about that that she paid, do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Did your mother or your father make any of your clothes in the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 My mother made quite a good few. Again, it was a case of having to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Do you think she didn't actually enjoy needlework?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Well, I wouldn't say she didn't. She liked making... she liked creating things for us then. It was a very simple way of being able to do 
something that she thought was worthwhile. We were poor, really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 I suppose being a painter and decorator there were times in the winter when your father wasn't working?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Sometimes not from just after the Fair, which was at the beginning of Septemb
er until near on Easter he would be out of work, and no dole, of course, in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 And nothing from his employers to tide him over?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Oh, no.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 They just laid people off, then, did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Oh, yes. He might have been taken in for a week
, say, somebody wanted their house decorated inside and might do away for a week; or they might have a cottage out in the country that the boss wanted repaired and decorated, and then he'd be asked to go out and he'd stay with them and then come back home
 at the weekend.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 But those would be pretty short?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12919142\charrsid3743759 During that period, how did your parents manage then, for money?}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Well, my father was a saving man, every penny possible. Nothing was spent in waste. In fact, he was rather the ot
her way, he was very tight. We had... before I remember we had my grandparents, my father's mother - she had a grocery establishment - and I think they used to have a little help from her, but I was very tiny then and I wouldn't remember it. This is what 
you're told in the course of people talking to you. I have an aunt, my mother's sister, lived out in the country on a big estate, he was a herdsman on a big estate, and she used to send vegetables, rabbit, chicken, anything and it did help.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 What about rent, did they have to pay rent for their house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes, a very small rent, compared with rents of today, anyway. The house belonged to an uncle of mine who lived in 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}London{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} and it was just a token rent, I would say, then, from a brother, but it was a rent.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Was this brother in much better circumstances, then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes, he had progressed and he was in rather a large office in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}
London{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. There again, being quite a small child at the time I can't tell you what, but yes, I would say they were in very much different circumstances to us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Was that a brother of your father's?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 That's right, yes, and older brother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 But mostly, I suppose, when they had to be paid out, it had to be what had been saved from the...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Oh, yes. Although, again....perha
ps remembering again, my father owned the house that had been left to him by his mother and once a quarter I used to go with Mother and we used to collect the rent. As far as I can remember that rent was somewhere about }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15153356 \'a3}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 1.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Not very much, but I suppose it helped.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 I can always remember seeing a golden Sovereign and that's all I can remember of it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Did they pay into any clubs? Slate clubs, or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 No. My father believed in saving his own money in his own way and then he knew he'd got it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 So it was all kept in the house, was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Did they ever have to get any help from any outside agencies at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 They didn't have any chance. There weren't any to get any from in those days. If you hadn't got it, you starved.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 If you were absolutely destitute, though, you could get sometimes relief, couldn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 I dare say one would have done, but my father would never have done.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 'Cos a lot of respectable people would never have considered it, would they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 No. No. My father was an Oxonian and he was full of pride.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Was he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes. Very proud man in his way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Proud of being from {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Oxford{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Well, yes, but.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes. Very reserved type. I'm afraid I haven't grown like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 You mean keeping himself to himself, that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Was he an easy person to talk to when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Not really. He loved us, but we could go to Mother, we couldn't go to Father. Father was the last one to approach.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Did you feel at ease with him when you were with him or were you...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 
Oh, I loved him. Oh, yes. Oh, he was wonderful, he was a wonderful father to me without any doubt, but as I grew older I realised just the withdrawal, then, of his mind, of his state.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Do you think he was depressed, at all? Was it anything like that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 
Oh no, no, just the personality and, as I've gathered from things that I've been told his brothers and sisters were exactly the same. You know, something that... I don't know, I can't tell y
ou because I'm not a bit like that, but... such a withdrawing state all the time. He didn't want anybody calling. He didn't want anybody coming in, he resented anybody coming into the house. He was quiet to them, he didn't go away but he was quiet to them
, but he just hated anybody coming in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Did this mean that not many people did come in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 
No, my mother's sisters came occasionally, his own sister would come, his brother would come occasionally, but we very rarely had any visitors.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 What about neighbours dropping in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Good gracious me, no!
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 
Was that unusual generally when you were a child, do you think, among the kind of people that your parents knew, or was it only in your particular household?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 I don't think so. Other people seemed to have friends that called occasionally, but you see, this was my father's attitude.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 But what about in the days he wouldn't be there, wouldn't they drop in on your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Possibly neighbours might come round. It was usually a neighbour with so
mething, to say to Mother, 'could you run this up on the machine for me, I've just had it given to me', or a pair of trousers to be cut down for a smaller son, something like that. Very rarely did anybody come. I don't remember seeing people sitting aroun
d in our house, anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 On this question of }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12919142\charrsid3743759 clothing}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 , you were saying how she would mend - she presumably did mending if she could sew, everyone had to then, didn't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 I know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 When she bought clothes - 'cos she did buy some clothes, didn't she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 She had to, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Did she buy new, or secondhand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 
When they were bought they were new. She wouldn't have gone to a jumble sale, she wouldn't have gone to a secondhand stall in a market, but we did have cast-offs from relations. Again, f
eeling no discredit about it. I wore my cousin's clothes and thought they were absolutely wonderful.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 But she wouldn't have bought them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Oh, no, no.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Where did she actually buy the clothes, was there a certain shop she used to go to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12919142\charrsid3743759 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759  shops on the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Cowley Road{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, one was \{BLANK\} and the other was a shop that is still there now, {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Capes{\*\xmlclose} on the \{BLANK\} Road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 And shoes, what about them? How were shoes got?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Again, from shoe shops in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Cowley Road{\*\xmlclose}
{\*\xmlclose}. They were good, strong, sturdy ones.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Did you have shoes for every day and another pair for Sundays, or...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Oh, yes, always a different pair for Sunday. Yes, different clothes, different shoes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Now what happened when the Sunday shoes grew too small? This must have happened quite soon, I suppose, if they were only worn once a week.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 
Most probably they were passed on to somebody else. This was done quite openly between relations, with no thought that you were doing them a charity.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 When there were jobs to do in the house, you k
now, like cleaning, cooking, washing up, those sort of things, did your mother do it all or did your father help her at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Occasionally Father would help, but I would say mainly Mother did the lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 You don't think your father had any regular duties in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 What about things like decorating and repairs and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12919142\charrsid3743759 handy work}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 ? You know, that kind of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Well, of course, he was very good at that type of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Because it was his job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Because it was his job, although th
ey say that the cobbler's children were the worst shod; I think that our house was most probably the worst decorated, except for a little bit of paint now and then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 But he did do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Did he ever do anything for you children, like dressing you, putting you to bed, that type of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Oh, yes, he would take me to bed. That's one of my very happy memories, I think.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Can you tell me about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12919142\charrsid3743759 Yes, after a little bit of supper - it was always a little bit of supper, not l
ike children of today when they say they don't have any supper - always afterwards it was, 'Daddy, are you ready for me?' and he always used to carry me to bed, usually pick-a-back. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 
Oh, yes, one of my very happy memories, that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 That was a regular thing, was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Until about what age?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Oh, I suppose 8 years old.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 You would be already in your night clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Oh, yes, dressed ready for bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Was there a set time for going to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Round about {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 8}}}8 o'clock{\*\xmlclose}, I suppose. I was put to bed in good time, I wasn't allowed to stay up very late.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Do you ever remember him reading to you, or telling you stories?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Oh, yes, we used to have stories of his boyhood days, when he was down by the river; and he would sing. My mother woul
d sing to me, as well. All the old type songs, when I hear them now my memory goes back to and ask for a special song.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 By 'old type songs' do you mean old folk songs, or all types of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 All types of things, like The Volunteer Organist and then some of the music hall songs, 'Daisy', and 'The Man Who Broke The Bank at 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Monte Carlo{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}' was one of my father's favourites. He was an instrumentalist as well, he could play many instruments, string and wind instruments.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Did he play quite a lot?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 When he was older, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 But when you were a child, did he not play so much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 
Sometimes, yes, he'd bring his violin down off the wall and say 'what shall I play you today'. Then another time I'd say 'will you bring your cornet down and will you play some of ...' as I used to call it "Dolly Carte's". He used to play the operas, }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12919142\charrsid3743759 D'Oyley}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759  Carte, Gilbert and Sullivan.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Had he ever belonged to a band or an orchestra?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 He and his brothers and a couple of friends had a small string band and they us
ed to entertain some of their friends, you know, on a Saturday night, and their works parties and things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 What about your mother, did she play at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 No, no. I think that there was never any chance, but she had a very nice voice. She u
sed to sing very well. But again in the circumstances that she lived in before she was married she hadn't a chance. When you're in service you don't have an awful lot of chance to do that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 He had a cornet and a violin? Anything else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 He had... let me see. Violin, cornet, a melodeon, ocarina, tin whistles galore, flute.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 And he could play all those?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Did he teach you and your brother and sister to play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 No, I tried the violin, but it was no good, it was too much
... there was too much scraping about it. I learnt the piano when I was small, but I liked singing better.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Where did you learn the piano? Who taught you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 A Miss Scarsbrook who lived on the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Cowley Road{\*\xmlclose}
{\*\xmlclose}. When she found I'd got a voice I used to do voice singing at her house when I did piano work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Your mother paid for that, did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Quite an achievement, really. It shows how careful they must have been to afford things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes, it was quite a lot when you knew the circumstances that you were living in, she did quite a lot for we children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12919142\charrsid3743759 You, yourselves, in the home, did you have do any jobs? }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 
Did you have any set duties?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 No, I'm afraid I was a lazy child! (laughter) Mother used to say }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5796645\charrsid3743759 \lquote }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 get your hands away I'll do it'. Sometimes, later on when I got a bit older, in my 'teens, I was told if I wanted friends in the front room I would have to dust it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Because it was only used infrequently, I suppose?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes, oh, very.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Sundays, I suppose, would it be?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes, and Christmas time; holiday time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 
Your elder brother and sister, do you remember them having regular jobs, or was it the same with them that your mother found it easier to do things herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Oh, I don't think any of us really did anything much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Did they look after you at all? Do you remember them doing anything like minding you as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes, my sister had to take me out, and especially on a Sunday, but it didn't go down very happily when she got a bit older. I was always the
 nuisance. I was always doing the wrong thing. Oh, yes, that was her duty, to look after me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 She really found this rather a chore, did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Well, yes. Again, they were fond of me, I was the baby of the family and they were fond of me and all the 
rest of it, but I was still a blooming nuisance.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 That was on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 
Yes, Sunday especially. Sunday afternoon. She used to find it irksome when she was in her 'teens because she and her girlfriends wanted to do far more than take a youngster around with them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 
What about when you were actually a baby? Of course, you wouldn't remember this, but do you know if she took you out in the pram at all, or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Oh, yes. They were allowed to take me out round what was called }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12919142\charrsid3743759 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Randelgh}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759  Square{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, which was {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Randelgh Street{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Green Street{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Leopold Street{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} and back on to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Cowley Road{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 And things like feeding you and looking after you, and mothering, did she do much of that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 I think very little. That was a mother's duty. Again, it wasn't pushed on to other children, not in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 What about you, yourself, do you remember doing errands for her or little jobs for her, or for your brother, at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Well, errands, yes, to the shops. Of course... naturally, being on Cowley Roa
d we were quite near the shops, and sent with a little note to the various... to the grocer's, the newsagents, the sweetshop, occasionally, and perhaps down the road to get a reel of cotton, but never to do anything in large shopping, just a few pence in 
your hand.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Did you ever do any errands for neighbours for money, or anything like that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Just for the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Do you ever remember your father taking you out on his own? I mean without your mother, just on his own.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 
Oh, yes, before my mother's birthday especially he always took me down the round and asked me what I would like to buy Mother for her birthday. Sometimes we'd go and look in the china shop, which was {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Butler{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}'s at the corner of {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Chapel Street{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} and find..
. oh, perhaps a nice plate that I would like to buy her. I have one in my sideboard cupboard now that I bought for her when I was quite a tiny child. I think it was the first big thing I bought her. I was taken down right to the bottom of 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Cowley Road{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} once to buy a nice handkerchief that I'd seen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 You must have enjoyed that. What about paying for it? I mean, where did the money come from for that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Father would make quite sure that the money would be there. I didn't have any money. I think I had abo
ut a penny a week, and a farthing occasionally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 The penny was fairly regular, was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 
Oh, yes. We had just a little amount of pocket money and there was a very kind uncle, too, that would give me a penny or take me along to the sweet shop, which used to go about....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 What did you do with the penny?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Oh, buy lots of things. I think we could buy }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12919142\charrsid3743759 3}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759  or }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12919142\charrsid3743759 4}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 
 things for a farthing in those days; little tiny strips of chewing gum, and toffee, all sorts of .... At}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3743759  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12919142\charrsid3743759 Easter}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759  time little sugary straights; Christmas time, sugar mice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 What about the birthdays of your sister and brother, were they given presents by you at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 No. I suppose occasionally Mother might have been able to make something or buy something at the penny bazaars that would be
 around at that time, and then it would be wrapped up and given to me, and say, 'This is for Lou tomorrow, it's her birthday' or 'Jim's birthday will be tomorrow and he wants this'. It was usually bought for me, but as far as having money to buy anything 
with, that was out of the question altogether.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 And on your birthday did you receive presents from the...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 
Yes, all the family would give something, only a small thing like a little jigsaw puzzle, or perhaps a little handbag that my sister had made for me. There was always something.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 
Did your mother ever go out when you were a small child leaving you in charge of your father? I mean for a day, say, or an afternoon, that kind of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 No. Mother never went away at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 She didn't go out visiting on her own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 
No. Well, she might have gone out - while my father was at work she might have gone out to meet a friend, or see a friend in an afternoon, but it was always made quite sure that she was back before Father came home, and before we came home from school.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 She would have considered that important, would she, to be home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes, it was essential that she should be there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 For your father as much as for you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Oh, yes. She'd not think of being late when she knew that we
 would be home from school. I think only once do I remember her being later than I was one afternoon from school. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12919142\charrsid3743759 That stands out rather vividly in my memory, that does.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 You came home and found her not back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 It was terrible 'cos she wasn't there 
and I couldn't open the door. She was only, I suppose, minutes behind me, but because Mother wasn't there...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 And weekends, then, she was always around, was she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 You were saying how your father used to take you up to bed; did you have a room which you shared with others in the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 
When we were very small the 3 of us slept in the one room, in one bed. And then, as we progressed... as my sister got older she had a small bedroom to herself and my brother had the large bed by himself and I had a very small bed by the side.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 There were 3 bedrooms, I think you said?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes, Mother and Father had a very large bedroom, the front one and we shared the other...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Did you have the weekly bath system that so many families had in those days? Or did you have them other times?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 
I must say we had infrequent baths. I'm not going to pretend that we had a weekly bath (laughter). We had a jolly good wash always. That was an essential thing for us, as far as my mother was concerned that we
 had a jolly good wash. But I won't say a weekly bath.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Could you hazard a guess as to how often you did have them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Oh, sometimes once a fortnight, sometimes once in 10 days; if it was very, very cold Mother didn't believe that we should be strip
ped off, so it has been 3 weeks.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Because rooms would have been cold then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Well, there were no bathrooms. We had }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12919142\charrsid3743759 a hip}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759  bath in the kitchen, with the gas stove put on to give us warmth.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 What about clean clothes, can you remember what her system was with clean clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 
Oh, a weekly wash. I think, perhaps, the only things that weren't washed as regularly as might be were the stockings. They were the thick, black, woollen kind and I don't think they got washed as often as I would like them to, anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 But it was a change a week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 On the question of food, then, you had a kitchen. Did you eat there, or was that just for cooking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 No, that was a scullery kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Was the cooking done there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes, cooking was there. There was just the gas stove.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 So she had gas, did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 
Yes. We often had - on Sundays - the joint roast on the spit in front of the fire. I think my husband would have told you about this with his house, as well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 It was the same one as he described to me, turned a certain number of times.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 That's right, yes, that's right. We used to think that this was rather nicer than having it done in the gas oven.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 I should think it tasted very good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Oh, yes, lovely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Did you always have a joint on Sunday, was that a regular thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 As regular as I can remember.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Even during the hard months?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes, even during the hard times; and we always had the cold for supper, and when I was married I was very surprised when my husband
 said that he wasn't used to this. I was doing the same as we'd done at home for years, bringing the cold joint on to the supper table.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 On a Sunday night, you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 On a Sunday night, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 What would he have been used to, then, just bread and butter...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Well, \{BLANK\}, bread and butter, bread and cheese, I suppose, but he was most surprised when I trotted the cold joint out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 What would you have had with it then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Oh, the cold potatoes, if there were any cold potatoes or cold greens... just a little bit of cold supper.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Would there have been any salad in the summer months at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes, possibly. We had a little garden. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12919142\charrsid3743759 Father used to grow a few lettuces. }
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 He used to grow mustard and cress, perhaps to see the joy in our faces when the mustard and cress began to grow. A few radishes, perhaps, in a flower pot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Did you help at all in the garden, then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Well, the garden where we lived on {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Cowley Road{\*\xmlclose}
{\*\xmlclose} was so small and there were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12919142\charrsid3743759 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759  high walls on each side that nothing, reall
y, grew properly. But he loved his flowers so he used to have flower pots outside the kitchen door on stands so that we could have a little bit of green and a little bit of colour.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Did he ever have an allotment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 I suppose it was too small to keep any livestock of any kind? Even birds?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 We used to have rabbits.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 For the table, or for pets?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Well, sometimes they became table (laughter). They started as pets. And my brother had tame rats, he had a flawless white rat once upon
 a time; and he used to keep tame mice, as well. But again, this was only occasionally. But the rabbits were a pretty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 What about pigeons, or anything of that type?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Most of the vegetables then, I suppose, had to be bought?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 What about fruit, was there a fruit tree of any kind in the garden?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 No, only an elderberry tree.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Did it bear?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Oh, yes. It used to come in occasionally with an apple pie. Mother used to put the elderberries with the apply pie, and also they
 used to drop some into a bread pudding and that tasted jolly nice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Did she make wine at all with the elderberries?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes, yes. When Aunt sent her some fruit from the country she'd send, perhaps, some of the bruised fruit from the orchards there an
d then my mother would set to and make some wine and jam.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Did she ever use the elderberries for wine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Oh, yes. That's where I learnt my wine-making from.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 When would this wine be drunk? On what sort of occasions?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Oh, just when Father fancied a drop of wine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Quite regularly, then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 
Oh, yes, yes, quite often it would be brought out, if any visitors did come, Father's brothers or any of Mother's sisters, they might have a drop of wine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Did they buy any other drink to keep in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 
No. Father used to go out and have a drink of beer occasionally. In fact, he liked his drink of beer. When you bought it at 2d. a pint, you know, it wasn't too bad.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 What about your mother, did she like a drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 She never went with him to the pub?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Oh, good gracious me, not in those days! Again, you see, this is how it keeps running through 'not in those days'.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Respectable women didn't?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Do you think none of your mother's friends ever went, either, the people that she knew, they wouldn't have gone along?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 I think the people that my mother associated with would not have gone to a public house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 If they wanted a drink anywhere, how do you think they got one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 We wouldn't have gone, but Father m
ight have gone down to what is commonly known as The Rat's Hole - it was known as The Rat's Hole, always has been - and he would have taken a jug down and got a jug of beer and brought back home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 And they'd have a drink together, then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 On the question of meals, again, you were saying about the joint on Sunday; did you have a cooked midday dinner when you were children?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Oh, yes. It might have been stew; it might have been a good vegetable soup; might have been breast of lamb, something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 She knew how to cook cheap things, then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 
Well, you see, she herself had been a cook. She knew the best cuts, she knew the cuts that would last the longest and she was a very wise woman as far as cooking was concerned.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 The vegetable soup that you had would that have had anything else with it or would it just have been the main...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 
It would have been the main course because perhaps at that particular part of the week there was nothing else in the house, so this would be the main meal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Would you have had bread with it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 And anything else at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 
Possibly a good plum duff, or something like that, after. Oh, yes, there would have been a pudding that would have been sustaining enough. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 And what about other days when you had, say, a more filling first course, like stew, would you have had a pudding then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Oh, yes, always had a pudding.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Plum duff, and what other pudding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Bread pudding - we were very fond of bread pudding; and roly poly p
uddings, and steamed puddings; pastries - jam and possibly a closed tart, you know; mince tart.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Were there vegetables on those days at midday, if there wasn't a vegetable soup?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 I can never remember a dinner without vegetables.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 And potatoes, I suppose?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 And then for your evening meal - you were saying on Sunday you'd have the cold roast - what would you have on another day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Normal days, bread and cheese. Not bread, butter and cheese; bread and cheese, and I always remem
ber my father saying at the times when we said could we have a bit more cheese, we were always told that we must eat our bread and smell our cheese so that it made it go round. We only had a small piece of cheese, I can assure you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Did you have anything to drink with it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes, cocoa.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 At what sort of time would that be, that you had the evening meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Just before 8 o'clock, just before... we were put to bed then, just before 8 o'clock, bedtime.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Between your dinner and then, did you have tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 
Oh, yes, we had tea, mother made a pot of tea for us when we got home from school and my father would most probably be a bit later, so he would have had his tea, perhaps, when we'd finished. But again, as a small child, I never remember my fath
er sitting down to tea without my mother eat with him, and if he had an egg for his tea then he wouldn't let me sit there without giving me some of it. I had to have a piece of bread with some of his egg on it. He wouldn't eat alone.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Do you think he felt it was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12919142\charrsid3743759 ill-mannered}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759  to do so?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 
I think so, yes. That was one of my father's standards. He didn't like eating alone, he didn't think he should be eating when other people weren't. Other people should share with him. Although he knew that we had our 
share, really, but always had the... whoever was there, whether it was my brother, my sister and I, we would always be sharing with him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 And on the whole he would have the same kind of thing that you were having, would he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Possibly, yes, but wher
e he would have had the privilege of having an egg we most probably would have bread and jam, or bread and treacle, or even bread and lard.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Did you have much butter in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 We had a little butter. Margarine... although I suppose in those days I wouldn't have known it was margarine, but if Mother had some nice }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5796645\charrsid3743759 p}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 
ork dripping - beef dripping, too - we would prefer to have bread and dripping and I know, myself, asking for bread and lard if I didn't want bread and butter.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Your butter might have been margarine, you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 It might have been. Possibly... as I say again, in my childhood days I possibly wouldn't even have known.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Did you ever have a drink of milk?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Very rarely. Very rarely, I think, milk. Very weak tea. We were never allowed to have strong tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 That's what you had at teatime?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 
Can you think of breakfast, now? I think that's one meal we haven't talked about. Did you all have that together, as family, or did your father go out earlier?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Father would be out early, he would sometimes have to be out at half past }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12919142\charrsid3743759 6}
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759  in the morning to get to work, because he might have }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12919142\charrsid3743759 5}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 
 or 6 miles to walk before he got to where he was working. And we 3 children would have breakfast together, Mother would have had hers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Would she have had something with your father before he went off, do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 
No, I think she would have seen him off first and then she would have sat and had a little bit of bread and butter. It wouldn't have been much more than that. I don't ever remember having bacon when I was a child, not when I was small.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 And what about egg or sausage for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 We might have had... Sunday, perhaps, we might have had sausage for breakfast, or a boiled egg, but in the week it would have been
 bread and butter, perhaps a little bit of jam or marmalade.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 And tea, again?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Did your father then take his breakfast with him to have when he got there?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Oh, no, he would have had it before he went. But he would take a hunk of bread and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12919142\charrsid3743759 cheese}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759  for his lunch, for midday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 And then what did he have for his dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 
If he was away from home it would be sandwiches with a little... perhaps with a bit of yesterday's meat in it, or perhaps a little bit of corned beef bought from th
e grocery shop if Mother knew he was going to be away. Or again, he might have had an egg put into sandwiches. But he always took something, again, like eggs which was fairly }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12919142\charrsid3743759 substantial to}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759  last him until he came home somewhere around about 5, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12919142\charrsid3743759 6}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759  o'clock.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 On those days, was it more often than not that he took a cold lunch - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12919142\charrsid3743759 cold}
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759  dinner - or was it usual for him to come home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes, I would say mainly sandwiches. It was very rare that he was near enough to come in for a midday meal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 And so then in the evening he would just have the cold tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 People didn't worry so much then, did they, about hot meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Oh, no, they were quite content. Bread was the staff of life they'd been told, and that was it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Did your mother bake at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Oh, yes, quite a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Cakes and that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes, cakes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 And bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Bread sometimes, not very often, but sometimes she have a little spasm, but cakes, always cakes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 She didn't buy cakes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Did she ever buy any tinned food?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 I don't think there was any in those days, when I was small.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 I was wondering about the corned beef, if that would have been in a tin?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Well, originally, I suppose, it would have been in a tin, but no, it was cut to order.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 You don't remember tins around, in the house?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 I don't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Because there was a little around at that time, according to food...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Well, about the only thing that I remember actually having on the table that was in a tin were the small tins of 
paste, of fish paste and meat paste, but there was not an awful lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Not sardines, or pilchards or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Possibly herrings in tomato sauce, yes. But we had very little in tins, in fact is was very occasional.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Did she ever pickle anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 
Yes. There again, when Aunt sent her things from the country, onions, shallots, an occasional pickle cabbage - red cabbage. Oh, yes, she was very provident, you know, always looking for the best thing to do for the family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Do you remember if she had any home recipes, or anything, if any of you were ill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 
Yes. She always used to cut pieces out from 'The People', the Sunday paper, it always had a column for the kitchen. She always had a doctor's book in the house....no, not a doctor'
s book, it's really something to try and remember what this was. It was a book that was given at the chemist with something that you bought. I can't remember if it was Payne's Syrup or whether it was Scott's Emulsion, but it gave you all the various thing
s to do when people had bronchitis and things like that. And it was... only in herbal remedies.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 And she kept these, did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes. When we had a cough she would make things up, like turnip syrup. Cut the turnips up and put sugar in and then we used
 to have syrup from the turnip, and that relieved the throat. We had brimstone and treacle, all those sort of things, you see, that were more or less the natural thing for the families to do in those days. Not to... well, you couldn't afford to run for th
e doctor because you had to pay him every time and if you hadn't got the money you couldn't pay him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Was there a doctor's club of any kind that people paid into?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 No. Or at least, I don't ever remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 So she didn't call the doctor when you had a pain?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Unless it was absolutely necessary.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 What was her feeling about table manners? Both your mother and your Father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Oh, they were both very strict. Very strict on table manners.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Can you tell me something about what they considered important about table manners?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 
Not making a noise with your soup. Anyone made a slurpy noise we were reprimanded by Father. We must not put arms on the table. You must not reach across the table for something that you wanted, you must ask for it, a
nd you had to sit properly, not lean on the table and gaze around. You were at table to eat and to eat properly. You mustn't sing. If you felt like singing something and burst out into song you got one big glare from Father. They were very strict indeed o
ver that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 You mentioned your father twice just then, was it your father who was the main one to enforce these rules?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes. Although I don't ever remember my father laying a hand on us, he only used to look at us and just say one word, 'No!' Or he m
ight threaten to throw a bush at our heads, if we were very bad, and that was dreadful.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Do you ever remember him doing it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 He never did. He didn't need to, but we knew very well that we mustn't do it again. Mother was not quite so strict, but I f
elt her hand once or twice, but she was much more placid.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 What about talking at meals, were you allowed to talk?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Never?
