\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Did you talk much to her when you and she were together I mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 She was quite a good conversationalist was she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes she was a good conversationalist and I was a devil for talking.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 You mentioned you had 'The People' on a Sunday, did you have a daily newspaper as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes. I couldn't tell you what it was though. I only know it was a daily paper.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes, and any books in the house? Did anyone read books?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 
Yes. I think mother would have had a Christian novel or something of that kind. My father didn't read, but we had books. The old classics in the bookcase in the sitting room and we were
 always taught to read things like 'Black Beauty', 'Little Women', and 'Treasure Island'.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes. You had copies in the house that belonged to you or did you borrow them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Possibly those that we'd had given to us for presents. Birthday presents, Christmas presents.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 
'Uncle Tom's Cabin' was one of my gifts that I had from Sunday School. If you made regular attendance you always had a prize at prize giving time and I think I had a prize every year that I was at Sunday School, and it was us
ually a book. They usually gave you a book of some kind.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes. Did your mother read the books to you or your father read them aloud?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Mother, yes, used to do a lot of reading.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes. Do you remember her and your father ever reading aloud to each other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Do you remember a funeral in the family when you were up to thirteen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 My first funeral that I remember was my baby brother. I would think I was about }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12919142\charrsid3743759 5}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 , when he was born. I can remember seeing him. In my mind now I have a picture
 of him. Very vivid. As a tiny baby in the bedroom just after he was born, with the midwife bathing him. I remember too, in the sitting room when he died}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11477449\charrsid3743759 ,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759  a set of coffins on the sitting room table and the person that had been the midwife taking me in to kiss him because apparently this was something that was done.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes. How soon was this after the birthday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 I think he could have only lived within a month.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 There was something wrong internally. Again, I don't know what. I can remember
 my aunts sitting along the room side by side. They were going to the funeral with mother. I think perhaps that's the only one I can remember as a child except the aunts that lived away from us and I had seen the funeral cortege leave the house.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes. But that's all you have a memory of? Do you remember how you felt about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Well I was very sad that my baby brother had gone.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Oh very sad, because I thought this was lovely to have a baby. Again, it was like another big doll to me you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes. Did your mother talk about it to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 No. I don't remember her talking to me except to say that Jesus wanted him more than she did and so that's why he went.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes. That was quite the usual explanation then for children wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Oh yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 And still is. And do you remember in anyone in the family wore black or any kind of mourning clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Oh I would say they all wore black, and whenever there was a funeral of any relative everybody wore black. You wouldn\rquote 
t have thought of going to a funeral without black. All the men wore black arm bands and black ties and black ties and black bowlers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Even the children? Do you think even your brothers would have worn a black arm band?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 And what about in the days following? Would any of them have worn black. Would your mother have worn ordinary clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Not to any funeral.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 In the following days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Well it would have been black for quite a while.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes. Did your mother take you out, or your father take you out very much visiting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Not visiting.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 No. Out in the country for example?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Did you ever go out in the country?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Oh, we never went away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 No. We were what you would call a housebound family I would think, ex
cept when I went to school and started going out to my friend's house. I was more often in my friend's house than I was at home, during day-light I mean.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 But we used to go out walking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes. Saturdays and Sundays, especially Saturday afternoons when my father would get himself ready and we'd walk for miles.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes. The whole lot of you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Well yes. But then as my brother and sister got older I was the one that went. In the summertime we went to cricket matches out in th
e country.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Take a picnic tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Would you go all the way on foot?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 What sort of distances would you cover?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Well anything up to 4 miles when I was quite small.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Mind you I'd probably end up having a pick-a-back }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12919142\charrsid3743759 somehow}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759  or other. And then I was taught that my feet were made for walking.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 
Perhaps we'd go along Garsington Road up Cowley. Along Garsington Road to Littlemore and back down again to Headley Road and to home. Another time we'd go along the river over to Headington back along the road St. Aldgates and home that way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Oh we'd walk quite a long walk.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes. Did you ever stop anywhere and have tea or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 No. Once again, there was no money to do it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 No. And Bank Holidays? Did you do anything then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Oh we went to a fete.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 
Sometimes at Whitsun we went down to the river to see the regattas. Easter time possibly just a walk through the park. August it was usually some horticultural show or a fete in somebody's field somewhere.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes. There were usually outings then on Bank Holidays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes. Oh yes. This was the day when one looked forward. That this was going to be a special day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes. And you didn't go away ever for a holiday at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 
From the age of 12. My first holiday away from home was with my aunt that lived at Burcot, and I thought that this was absolutely wonderful and my first words to my aunt were 'I'm going to stay with you a week'.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 This was the one that always sent the produce?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes. This was the one that always sent the produce of course; they lived in a tied cottage to a farm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 My uncle was herdsman there and I thought that this was absolutely wonderful. When I went into her sittin
g room the smell of apples and lavender - I've got this in my mind the memory of it - and it was a beautiful country smell.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 And I did stay with her for a week and I used to be shipped over to her every so often after that for holidays. Mainl
y we used to go in a carrier's cart and come home in a carrier's cart.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes. Had you had much to do with her before then? I suppose you'd not seen her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 She used to come into Oxford occasionally, again by carrier's cart, and then if she came to Oxf
ord she always called at mother's first and then she called at my grandmother who lived down by the station.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 And we kept in tough with Aunt }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12919142\charrsid3743759 Rachel}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 . She was one of the favourites I think of the family you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 And I know her more than any of my aunts.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes. What sort of things did you do during that week? Can you remember? While you stayed at your aunts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Oh well, of course, there were the fields to roam in and if the field was being cut for grass you'd go and tumble i
n the hay. If it was after the corn had been cut you'd go and do a bit of gleaning so that you could help to feed uncle's fowl. You'd be able to go on to the farm occasionally and often have a ride on the horses as they were taking the hay back to the far
m.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 
And there was a river not very far away. You could go down to the river and fish in it, or down to the little pond to fish. There was always plenty to do. You were never at a loss for anything to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 No. Did she have any children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 She had one girl and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12919142\charrsid3743759 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759  boys - the boys were my age.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 In the other }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12919142\charrsid3743759 3}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759  tied cottages, that were (it was in a terrace) there were other children as well. There used to be about }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12919142\charrsid3743759 8}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759  of us so we joined in together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes. And do you remember, did anyone else ever go with you on your visits to your aunt or was it just you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 
The first time my sister took me because I had been so disappointed that I didn't think I was going to be able to go, and so my mother said to my sister "well get yourself 
ready and you can take your sister". And it was the only time I went by train. And I was told, "we'll go by train, and if we go by train you've got to walk and you've got to walk }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12919142\charrsid3743759 3}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759  miles before you get to auntie's house", and I said "I don't care I can do it", because I wanted to go so badly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 And you walked from Culham?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 
From Culham station up to Burcot, yes. And I was tired but I didn't think it was too bad. But otherwise I used to be just put on the carrier's cart in charge of Mr. Rogers either way.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes. And can you tell me in those days on Sundays did your parents attend a chapel or church at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 No. But they were very strict about we children going.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 To Sunday School in the morning and on to the Chapel Service and the c
hildren were released half way through the Chapel Service. Sunday School in the afternoon but in the evening we stayed at home. We weren't allowed to play games on Sunday like you did during the week day. You'd got to sit quietly and read a book. It was S
unday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes. Would your mother have done the same amount of work, housework and things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 
Oh she wouldn't have done any washing and she wouldn't have done any housework. She might have swept through but nothing was done on Sunday that should have been done during a week day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 No. And when you went to Sunday School did you go with the choir? You mentioned you had quite a voice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 I was a member of the junior choir to begin with. That was a choir that was conducted by the soprano of the other cho
ir until I was old enough to go into the adult choir. Yes. I was a member of the junior choir and then I progressed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 I didn't ask you this. What denomination was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Congregational.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Congregational, yes. Were you paid at all to sing in the choir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 No. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 And did you have any choir treats, or any reward for your choir work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 
No. No I don't think we ever did. The only time where the choir performed with other choirs at the Town Hall I think we were given a box of chocolates by our choir master - that's the only thing I can remember having special.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes. Was there any Temperance Club or anything like that attached to the Church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 I belonged to a junior guild and a girls' club. There was a bible class that some of them used
 to go to - I didn't. But I belonged to the welfare, I was trying to think of the name. Yes the Congregational Welfare Club, and I joined I think when I was about }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11477449\charrsid3743759 12}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 e and stayed in it until I was somewhere about }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11477449\charrsid3743759 1}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12919142\charrsid3743759 8}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759  I suppose.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 What sort of things and activities did it have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Drama. We did lots of little plays and a few sketches. We did raffia work, needlework, art. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12919142\charrsid3743759 We were taught by 3 sisters who were school-teachers in their normal daily duties and 2 of their friends. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 A very happy time.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 How many evenings a week would you go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Twice a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Twice a week. Yes. You didn't belong to any clubs or Band or Hope or anything to do with getting children not to drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 I started Band of Hope, that was at the Methodist Church and in what is n
ow Rectory Road - Pembroke Street it was called in those days. I started Band of Hope but I liked the Congregational Welfare Club best.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 It was more entertaining. Not entertaining exactly, but it gave you something to think about. They'd alwa
ys got something for our hands to do. And for our brain to work on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes. What sort of things did you do at the Band of Hope then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 I can't remember anything much about Band of Hope but singing hymns and being taught to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Not so educational?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 No. It didn't satisfy me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 No. Did your mother and father ever say grace at meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 No. And did they teach you to say prayers at night when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes. You were taught to say prayers. Was that your mother or father that taught you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Father used to remind us that we must say our prayers but mother was always there to know that we did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 You mean that she was in the room with you? Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 And did you ever have family prayers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 No. Not as a family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 No. Do you remember any Sunday School outings at that time?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 
Yes. In the very young days we used to be taken in brakes, horse brakes from the Congregational Church to a field by Bartemas Close. And we had games and a tea, usually buns and 
nice pretty fruit cake, and cups of tea. That used to last from about half past }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12919142\charrsid3743759 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759  'til about half past }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12919142\charrsid3743759 6}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Did your mothers go along too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Oh yes, mothers could go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Did your mother go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes mother always made quite sure that she went with us. And when we grew older there was a trip up the river by houseboat to }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12919142\charrsid3743759 Newham}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 
The houseboat, you know, was more the old time steamer. It had a long pole at the back that was about all I can remember of it. We had cousins that lived near. 
They went and their mother and their grandmother and my mother always went together. And one thing that I can always remember my aunt that came saying "If you don't want your cake you give it to me." We knew that she'd got an extra big pocket in her dress
 so that she could make quite sure she could take enough cake home so that the kids could have some for Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 That was the outing for the older children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 That's right. The ones that they could trust to be on the river.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Rather than just running around.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Parents' Political Attitudes. I think you said your parents weren't particularly concerned about politics?
