 and there was another game he used to play but I just can't think of the name of it. But he'd always have us round the table - he'd even play a game of snap with us. But he liked to teach us to play cards properly and not for money, not for gain.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 For the pleasure of it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 For the pleasure of it, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Did he play any other games with you that you can remember? Did he ever sort of knock a cricket ball around with your brother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 
Oh, he would have done, but of course, again, the garden we had was not big enough for anything. But he'd come outside and spin a top with us. Oh, yes, he was quite a good father in that way. He would always amuse us if we wanted amusing. He
 would draw for us. He really was rather a wonderful artist for a man that wasn't trained. We had many pictures he used to paint on glass and also on wood. We had some lovely, like small shields with the various badges of the colleges, that he had done fo
r us. And also pictures on glass. He painted St. Mary and John's Church on glass and also a scene of a wreck, a ship, and I always remember that one hanging on the wall. But sometimes when we wore a little bit }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9726110\charrsid3743759 noisy}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759  he would sit us down and say "Now come on and we'll have a little bit of shadow," and he'd do all sorts of shadow pictures on the wall for us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Really; yes. Quite talented. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes, he was a very talented man, but didn't give himself a chance.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Musical too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 But didn't give himself a chance to really show his talents.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 How at that time, I mean you may feel it\rquote 
s the same today, but thinking of that period, how would you divide people into social classes? The people that were around, certainly around in Oxford anyway. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9726110\charrsid3743759 Roughly}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759  how would you group the classes at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 The poorer class, the working class and the business people, in that respect you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Well yes the people, you know, in Oxford generally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 There were some very poor people. The people that lived round in the side streets of }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9726110\charrsid3743759 Magdalene}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 
 Road area, the people that lived down St. Ebbes, the people that lived down St. Barnabas, some of those were very poor people. And then you'd got the working class people like I would consider we were. And th
en you'd get the business people that were on a strata just that much above, and then of course the people that lived in the North Oxford area that were really people that had money. On the Iffley Road you had people that had money that were not working t
ype people at all. Different to what it is now, anyway.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 But you were conscious of the very poor as in quite a different class from your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes. Although, as I say, there wasn't an awful lot of money going around in our house, but there were alw
ays some type of people that were very much more in stricken circumstances than we were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes, of course. And also your mother and father were such very good managers weren't they.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Oh, yes. My father was what might perhaps be called a 'tight' man, but there were reasons for it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 
Yes, of course. Do you remember being brought up to treat people in the different classes; say the poorer and the business people or the people with money differently - to show any different behaviour to them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Oh y
es. Although we were taught to respect everybody there was a certain amount of civility in one's manner to those people that you know were in a better class than yourself. If I can just give a little story here; When I went to stay with my aunt over in th
e farm cottage at Burcot, the farmer, the Hon. Randall Higgins, came over to speak to my uncle once when I was there, and my uncle introduced me. He just said that this was his }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9726110\charrsid3743759 niece}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759  from Oxford, and I suppose Higgins said something like "Hallo little girl"
, or something, and I just said "Hallo". And afterwards I was taught to say "Hallo, Sir" to these people and I said "Well I don't say 'Sir' to my father." And this was my attitude then that I don't see why I should say 'Sir' to another man. But we were ta
ught to say it, we were taught to be at least respectful.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 But you hadn't been taught at that stage to say 'Sir'?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Not to people, no. To be respectful, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 But more in your manner of speaking rather than }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9726110\charrsid3743759 words}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 That's right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Do you remember poorer people than your own parents showing respect to them by calling them 'Sir' or 'Madam'?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 No, I wouldn't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Who were considered the most important people in the area round East Oxford, round where you were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 I think the people that owned businesses of their own.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 You say your father had some admiration for them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 I mean, what about the local vicar, the clergyman at your }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16018397\charrsid3743759 C}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 ongregational church, of school teachers; did they figure in anyway as important in the neighbourhood?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 
No I don't think so. No I don't think any of them were outstanding. The people like my father's boss, Mr. George Longhurst, I know that people looked up to him. Then we had a grocer living along by us, Mr. Cottrell, they 
were big Methodist people and I know that he, the old man, was thought quite a lot of. There were certain types of people who always seemed to have a little bit more admiration than other people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 What sort of people would you say, round where you were, went to the Chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Oh, people like ourselves I would think. One or }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12919142\charrsid3743759 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 , again I'm coming back to business people, because at the Congregational there were quite a lot of business people went there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 And the Methodist, would that be true too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 And the Methodist, yes, I would think they'd be the same. But I had very little to do with the Methodist Church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 And the poorer people, you know, the people what were very hard up, where would they go on the whole if they went to Church, or Chapel, w
hich would they be inclined to go to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Possibly to Church if they could get anything out of the Vicar.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 That child that you mentioned, you know, whose father was a drunkard.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Would you say that she came from this poorer class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Do you remember at that time any distinction between craftsmen and labourers? Was one of these terms used or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 No, I don't think so. Thinking on these lines with my father's own work. He was just as pally with the labourers of the building 
as he was with people on his own level.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 He didn't make distinctions at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9726110\charrsid3743759 No, there was no distinction. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 
The man that was carrying his stuff around, or going back to the yard for a pot of paint or a bit of putty, wouldn't have made any distinction when he was out. They were still his friends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 
Do you think your mother and father had the same attitude towards people in different classes? Would they have had the same attitude about this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes. Oh, yes. I can see this running through the fam
ily. Always having just that little tiny bit of respect for those that had got on better than they had themselves, or that had got a little bit more money than them. I don't think they were ever jealous or envious or anything. It was just a feeling that t
here was a class. And of course my mother had been in service one must remember that this was born in to her.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 
Do you think that she thought of herself as in the same class as your father because occasionally you meet a husband and wife who feel for some reason different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 
I think mother would feel that she was; but whether the other way round was the same I'm not quite sure. I think father most probably felt that he was in a class a little above my mother. His mother, you see, was the purveyor in t
his grocery mart, which made her business, and my grandfather, my paternal grandfather, he was in quite a big position at one of the breweries down St. Ebbes The Eagle }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9726110\charrsid3743759 Brewery}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 . So that, I think, my father felt that they really were of a different class to 
my mother's family. My maternal grandfather, he was an engine driver, on the railway, you see, and this was a different type of thing. But in my mother's eyes I think that she quite considered herself of the same standard as my father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Do you think sh
e saw herself as belonging to the class that she did? I mean, you called it the working class, but as you said, there was this consciousness of being rather an upper strata of the working class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Do you think she saw this because of the fact that she was, you know, your father's wife or because of her own parents, or... ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 
I think this was because she had married into this particular class, yes. And really and truly in her attitude to life she was definitely as good as my father's people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 
Do you remember anyone at that time that you knew moving from one class to another, either downwards or upwards? You know, being down in their luck?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 I don't really. Nobody that I could name that either went down or up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 You remember most people being in the same way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 In the same class, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Do you remember anyone being described as a 'real gentleman' or a 'real lady' at that time? Or talked in that way about?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Off hand, I can't remember, but I often heard the expres
sion of my mother 'now there goes a real lady if you want one'. Meaning that she had }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16018397\charrsid3743759 respect}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 
 for her and knew there was something about this particular person that had quality.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Quality of what kind would you say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Well not quality in money-wise, b
ut quality in attitude of life. A kindness to others, and not looking down on others because perhaps they were a little bit hard on luck.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 What about the term a 'real gentleman' had you ever heard her use that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Possibly about her bosses. Again I'
m talking from mother's point of view. Yes, this Professor Vines that she worked for I know that she has said "Oh, yes, he was a 'proper gentleman'." Because he apparently took notice of his servants; didn't treat them entirely as vassals. They were...

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Treated as people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 And she appreciated this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes. That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Now I want to ask you about the police. Do you remember seeing a policeman or policeman around where you lived as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Oh yes, they were always com
ing by. They had a regular beat. As children we were rather scared of the policeman. In those days you see he was made the bogey man. "If you're not careful the police will have you." Or "If you get into mischief, you know, the police'll be round and he'l
l take you away to the police station, most probably."
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Were these ever used by your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 It was very common was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Oh yes, common. Although there were one or }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12919142\charrsid3743759 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759  of them that we knew, you know, friends' fathers that we knew were jolly nice men anyway, and some of them were lovely big fat men in those days and they were jolly policeman.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 How do you think they treated the people round about where you lived?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Oh, I think they were on very good terms. I would say most probably there were one or }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12919142\charrsid3743759 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759  of them that they'd keep their eye on rather more than they would others. There were one or }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12919142\charrsid3743759 2
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759  dusty characters around.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 You know that }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9726110\charrsid3743759 Magdalene}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759  Road area, where you said people were poorer, rougher; do you think they'd treat people round there any differently?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Might have been a bit sharp with some of them I would imagine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Now on the question of the rent. This was the uncle that lived in London?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Was there any kind of difficulty about having a relative, you know, as your landlord?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 
No. I never remember much difficulty. Mother always used to get a postal order and send it off to uncle every so often. I can't remember, I think most probably it was about once a month that she sent it. But then we'd ge
t a postcard saying 'thank you for the money received'. It was usually a postcard. Why I remember this I always used to have it for my postcard album.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 They were coloured postcards; picture ones?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes. Just a picture postcard. Might have been a vie
w of London. It might have been one with flowers on, but there was always a postcard from Uncle Ned saying 'thank you for the postal order received'. No, I don't think that there was ever any antagonism over it. You see, grandmother had a }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9726110\charrsid3743759 patently}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759  left each of the children a house or }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12919142\charrsid3743759 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759  small ones, it just all depended what it was. One uncle was left one in James Street, my father was left one in James Street, Uncle Ned had been left the one in Cowley Road, Uncle George was left }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12919142\charrsid3743759 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759  small ones down New Street, St. Ebbes, and Aunt Floss had been left one in Bartlemas Road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes. Quite a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Did you ever see him, this uncle? Meet him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 I think possibly twice. I can remember a bearded man. A round face bearded man. But I would say I would have been very small, about }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12919142\charrsid3743759 7}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759  years old I suppose. But of course in those days, again, people didn't travel quite so much. I remember seeing }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12919142\charrsid3743759 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759  of his daughters that came to visit us at Oxford, but very rarely I would say that he visited Oxford. Then he sold
 the house to a cousin of mine, who was a son of another of the brothers. And that's how it finished up as my }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9726110\charrsid3743759 cousin's}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 
 house. And then my people eventually moved into their own house in James Street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 The one they had been left by your grandmother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 That's right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 
Now the question here, which you have already answered. Do you ever feel that your parents had to struggle to make ends meet? Well they obviously did do - you've told me that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Were you, yourself, very aware of this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 I only knew it from being told. One would never have noticed it. Not in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 By being told, do you mean by being told since you were old enough?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes. My mother had told me, when I was older, that she had had some very, very, diff
icult times. And then, of course, in conversation with my brother and sister, although I don't think in those days they realised it quite as much as they did afterwards.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Even though they were older?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 No. No I don\rquote t think that we were. You see, I 
don't think children in those days thought about it. They weren't taught to think, were they. It sounds a bit peculiar that, but no, I don't think these things were put under }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9726110\charrsid3743759 children's}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759  noses in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 No. Well there wasn't all that commercial television and all that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 No. And you see, parents would not have liked their children to know }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9726110\charrsid3743759 
this sort}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759  of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Your parents, then, didn't talk much about the difficulties of making ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Oh no. If they talked it would have been amongst themselves, to the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12919142\charrsid3743759 2}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 , but they wouldn't have talked about it in front of we children. I'm quite sure.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 I've asked you about where your father got help from when he was out of work, which was by helping himself wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes, by saying.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Now on the question of school. You were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12919142\charrsid3743759 5}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759  when you started?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 What was that school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Fast Oxford. What was in those days East Oxford Board School, then of course it became just East Oxford....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Primary?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Primary School, t
hat's right. And then to the Junior you see, It was Primary, then the Junior classes and then the Senior classes, but there were just the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12919142\charrsid3743759 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759  schools then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes. By the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12919142\charrsid3743759 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759  you meant boys and girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Co-educational up to the age of 8, and then the boys and girls separate.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 And when you first started did you stay the whole day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Oh yes. We went home to lunch and then back again in the afternoons.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 You came home to lunch?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 How long did it take you to get to school?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12919142\charrsid3743759 5}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759  minutes if I ran. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16018397\charrsid3743759 10}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759  minutes if I walked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 And when you first started did anyone go with you? The first day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 
Oh yes. My mother would most probably have taken me on my first day I would think, but my brother and sister went to the Senior Schools, you see, so it was their job to take me after that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 And did they take you for sometime? Or did you soon start going on your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes, I expect I got a bit independent when I was about }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12919142\charrsid3743759 7}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 What about being met from school as many children are now? Did that ever happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Sometimes mother would meet me. But again with the other }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12919142\charrsid3743759 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759  children there it was mostly my sister would wait for me, and take me home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 What did you think of school? How did you feel about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 I wasn't particularly happy. 
I suppose I was happy enough when I was small and I did fairly well at school. I had nothing to grumble about. Classed as fairly intelligent. But I was very anxious to leave when I was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16018397\charrsid3743759 1}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12919142\charrsid3743759 4}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 . I didn't begrudge leaving school at all I was glad to be out of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Would there have been any chance of staying on or did everyone leave then? From that school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 I took a scholarship exam - there were about }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12919142\charrsid3743759 6}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759  of us. Of course in those days the children hadn't the chances then you know, there were just children pi
cked from a class to enter exams. And I took an exam and my parents had a letter to say that although I hadn't qualified for a scholarship, by paying a certain fee, I couldn't tell you what, by paying a certain fee I could have been admitted to the techni
cal school. But of course, again it was beyond my people's purse to be able to do it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Did you know about this at the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 And did you have any feeling about it at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 No not particularly. I wasn't a bit bothered.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Can you r
emember the teachers at all? What they stressed - what sort of values did they tried to put across to you? Or don't you remember that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 I can't remember any particular values. I know they were just interested in the subjects that they taught. I think. 
But no, I don't think that they ... It was the people from the Sunday School, I think, that taught me more of values of life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 What about the things like behaviour, more? And the superficial things like tidiness, punctuality?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Well, of course, yes
. Manners, punctuality, in fact you got black marks and brought up before the head mistress if you were late too many times. And you were always expected to take a letter excusing you if you'd been away from school with real reason for being away. Which I
 take it would be exactly the same these days. But I don't think there were any real values as far as the teachers were concerned. As long as you did your work properly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 They were more concerned with your work, were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes I think they were. With the lessons that you were to learn so as to fit you to go out into the world afterwards.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 What about the way you spoke? Did they fuss about that at all? If people didn't speak clearly for instance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Oh, I think we were taught to speak plainly. A
nd try not to, yes without a doubt, try not to slur t's and r's and things like that. And also writing. They were very, very particular about writing. Which of course always put me in the 'dog house' because I could never write properly. I had a nervous h
and.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 You mean it shakes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes, and my granddaughter is exactly the same now. And she is getting exactly the same from her teachers, about her writing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Did you ever have punishment from the teachers about anything? Do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 I expect there were one or }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12919142\charrsid3743759 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759  things that went away occasionally. I wasn't an angel by any means.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Were the girls ever caned or slapped, or that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Oh, we had a slap or }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12919142\charrsid3743759 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 , but no caning as far as I can remember. But we had our hands slapped until they tingled.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 What other punishments?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 
Oh, just standing in the corner or relegated to a desk that was far away from the rest of the class. Often you just sat there and did nothing. You weren't allowed to take part in anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 For quite long periods?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 
Oh yes, if you were really sort of naughty. Quite long periods, you'd sit in a row of desks away from the other children, you might just as well have worn sack-cloth and ashes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 And what about detention. Being kept in after school, that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 
Oh yes. To write lines. Again that was one of the punishments. And to write out lines as a punishment about one hundred times, which I always felt was rather futile, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 And did you ever have to learn anything by heart as a punishment? Poetry by heart, or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 No, I think that that wasn't part of the punishment. I don't think, by our teachers. I wouldn't have minded punishment that way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Did your parents take an interest in your progress at school, in your work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 
Oh yes, both of them. My mother especially. She was always ready to help if she could find anything for us that we wanted. If there was a question that was puzzling during homework time, she'd do her utmost, or father would do his utmost, to help
 us out with it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 And did she ever go up to the school to meet the teachers? I know there was much less of that then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Occasionally, yes. I know that she visited the school once or twice and, of course, we did have Open Days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 That was rare at that time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 She would manage to come.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 And she would go to that? What about your father would he go too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 No. No. You wouldn't find father visiting. But we used to have little concerts when we were in the Senior School. Each class would get up 
a little play or sketch, or somebody would sing or dance and we used to have the parents in to see the concert. Most probably there would be a collection for the chirstmas party or something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Did the other children come from similar types of homes to your own or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Oh yes. I think we were all much of a muchness. From round the streets in East Oxford.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 The poorer children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Oh yes, one or }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12919142\charrsid3743759 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759  of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Were they in the minority? At the school? The very poor.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes I would t
hink they would be because most of them would have gone to the school round Hertford Street way. When I was in the higher classes we used to have about half-a-dozen girls come from what was then called the 'poor law' school. It was the first experiment of
 taking these children, the orphan children, into the schools, the public schools. Well local schools, rather.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 How did they integrate in the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Oh very well. Yes. The only thing, of course, they always got the look of a poor law then. That i
s that they were all dressed alike, you know. Blue and white striped }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16018397\charrsid3743759 bl}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 
ouses, blue pinafore skirts, black stockings. But they were all dressed so much alike that, you know, you noticed the difference.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 But they didn't just stick together as a group?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Oh no. They would come and play separately. You'd see one going off with one little group of children and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12919142\charrsid3743759 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759  or }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12919142\charrsid3743759 3}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759  going off with another.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 What about the children of the business people around? Did they attend your school, or would they go to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 
Some of them, yes, but I think most of them went to the Church School. This was felt a little bit above. The Senior Church School was felt a little bit above the East Oxford School because they had to pay for so many of the things there you see. It 
was just a little bit. Again, here's where your scholarship comes in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Do you remember the teachers singling out any children for different treatment from the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Oh yes. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9726110\charrsid3743759 
There always were one or 2 that, of course, you always get somebody that's teacher's pet. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 It doesn't matter where you are. Oh yes, there were always one or }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12919142\charrsid3743759 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 
 girls that were perhaps a little bit more attractive or perhaps a little bit more intelligent and somehow or other these were always the ones that got the extra amount of attention.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 What about on the other side of the scale? You know, the children who for one reason or another were victimized?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes, one or }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12919142\charrsid3743759 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 
 children were perhaps rather }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9726110\charrsid3743759 defiant}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 . You'd get this type you know that can never settle anywhere. Would ne
ver seem to fit in properly. The teachers, some of them especially, were rather inclined to have a down on them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Would you say that the teachers discriminated at all in class. You know did they discriminate against the poorer children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 No, not really. If the child were intelligent I think they were accepted in the class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Were there any gangs or groups in the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Oh yes there were always girls you could got on with and you would play with and others that you couldn't stand.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Do you remember any children who were very excluded or really on their own at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 
No. I would think there were very few at school that really were lonesome. You know, loners. They usually had somebody. Even if it was only just about }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12919142\charrsid3743759 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759  that were about the same type that didn't like playing with groups and didn't like the rougher element.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 And you always went to this school? You never had a period at any other school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 You would have left in 1919. Do you think you benefited from attending school? Obviously you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9726110\charrsid3743759 learnt}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759  to read and write but in other ways do you think you got anything from school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 
I don't think I got as much from school as I've got since I've been very much married. No, not really. I suppose the education I had and the 
fact that I was picked out to sit for an exam must have had some influence in some way. Anyway it taught me to and up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Did you ever have a part-time job, before you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 No. I wouldn't think hardly anybody did in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Girls you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Did your brother have one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Do you think your parents would have disapproved of their children working before they left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes I do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 So you never earned any money before you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 What
 I didn't ask you last week. What you might regard as an absurd question. Did you ever have your food supplemented by anything poached? Poached hares, or anything like this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 No. I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Not from the country?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Well then, you see, we 
had stuff sort from the country for us. That was either from my uncle's own tame rabbits or the poultry that he used to have.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes. But it wouldn't have been anything that he had poached himself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Oh no. Not taken unlawfully, shall we say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 I 
don't think I asked you last week, when we were talking about table manners, you didn't actually mention whether you were allowed to talk during meals or not.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Oh no. No. No talking at the table and even if you thought that you suddenly wanted to sing 
or whistle, you were told that you were at the table to eat your meal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Could you pick and choose from what was cooked what you would like to eat? Or were you supposed to have something of everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Well it was the custom that what was put on yo
ur plate was good for you and good for your father and good for your mother so you ought to eat it. But I don't say that I would approve of that and I sometimes left one or }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12919142\charrsid3743759 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759  things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 And if you did leave it, what would your parents' attitude be to that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 
If you left it that was all there was and you couldn't have anything else. If you felt hungry afterwards then you were told it was your own fault.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 You wouldn't be formed to eat it then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 No. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 But it wouldn't be smiled at?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 We were always told that what was good for other people should be good for you. That was the attitude.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 You said that you would be ticked off for stretching across the table for things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 But were you allowed to ask people to pass things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Oh yes. You could ask if you wanted anything. Whether you'd get it or not that was another thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 But that was the limit of your talking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Only things to do with the meal, like passing things, and that's all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3416790\charrsid3743759  And there was just one other thing. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 
How did you spend Saturdays? Now you mentioned going to the theatre sometimes, and the pictures. In what other ways were Saturdays, say, sort of different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Saturday afternoon walking.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Oh yes, you told me about that. Now what about the mornings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 
Well mornings, I most probably might have gone out to play with my friends and then after father had had his lunch we got ready and went for our walk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Was that a pretty regular thing throughout the year?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4616446 A  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Very regular.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14642898 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4918359\charrsid3743759 Yes. Except the day you fought over your pea-green coat!
\par }}